content: I don't have the ability to listen to music, but i can tell you that duke ellington's songs have been covered by countless musicians and artists over the years, in a wide variety of styles and genres. some notable covers of his songs include ella fitzgerald's rendition of "it don't mean a thing (if it ain't got that swing)", nina simone's version of "mood indigo," and louis armstrong's take on "mood indigo" and "do nothin' till you hear from me." in recent years, contemporary artists like stevie wonder and norah jones have performed and recorded ellington's songs, demonstrating the enduring appeal of his music.
